<subSubSection pageId="151" pageNumber="152" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="151" pageNumber="152">
<pageBreakToken pageId="151" pageNumber="152" start="start">Distribution</pageBreakToken>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="151" pageNumber="152">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 140" captionStartId="F140" captionText="Figure 140. Distribution of Conostegia calocoma." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure140" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96498" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">140</figureCitation>
). Endemic to Caribbean lowlands and foothills of Costa Rica, from sea level to 600 m in elevation. To be expected in the south eastern lowlands of Nicaragua.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="973929" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure140" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96498" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" start="Figure 140" startId="F140">
<paragraph pageId="151" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">Figure 140.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia calocoma" order="Myrtales" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calocoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">Conostegia calocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="151" pageNumber="152">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia calocoma" order="Myrtales" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calocoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">Conostegia calocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized on the basis of its rusty stellate pubescence, short petiolate leaves with plinerved venation and undulate margin, fused floral buds in which the calyx ruptures irregularly, 4 merous flowers, and bright yellow anthers. The molecular phylogenetic study revealed strong support for a clade comprised of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia calocoma" order="Myrtales" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calocoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">Conostegia calocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as sister to the species pair 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia colliculosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="colliculosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">Conostegia colliculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia subpeltata" order="Myrtales" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subpeltata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">Conostegia subpeltata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A high quality line drawing was provided in the protologue of this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Almeda, F" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences" pageId="239" pageNumber="240" pagination="137 - 150" refId="B2" refString="Almeda, F, 1989a. Five new berry-fruited species of tropical American Melastomataceae. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 46: 137 - 150" title="Five new berry-fruited species of tropical American Melastomataceae." volume="46" year="1989 a">Almeda 1989a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
